<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,1642,1698]" lastBlockId="13.[144,1104,167,639]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="2152" pageId="12" pageNumber="2151">
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[297,423,1642,1666]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="8.[212,279,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[220,1161,172,1288]" captionTargetId="figure-144@8.[219,1163,171,1284]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 2. Adults of Epichostis spp. (A) E. wufengensis, sp. nov.; (B) E. magnimacularis, sp. nov.; (C) E. tympanias (Meyrick); (D) E. proximitympanias, sp. nov.; (E) E. termitruncatula, sp. nov.; (F) E. termiprotrusa, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217046/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="2151">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
). Wing expanse 18.0–19.0 mm. Head yellow-white, grey-brown behind vertex. Antenna with scape deep grey on dorsal surface, yellow-white on ventral surface; flagellum pale grey-yellow, with fuscous annuli on dorsal surface. Labial palpus white; second segment with basal three-quarters brown on outside; third segment with a brown ring at base, pale yellow with scattered brown scales distally. Thorax and tegula yellow-grey, yellow-white posteriorly. Fore wing ground colour greybrown; costal margin gently arched, basal one-third fuscous, distal two-thirds deep yellow; termen truncate, black, bordered by yellow-white along inner side; longitudinal inconspicuous pale yellow fascia along subcosta; two large black ventral patches edged with yellow-white: first one irregularly triangular, from between base and onethird upward exceeding slightly one-half width, outer margin arched; second one irregularly trapezoidal, extending from between ventral one-third and three-quarters upward exceeding three-quarters width, outer margin protrudent dorsoapically; cilia grey-white. Hind wing and cilia grey tinged with pale yellow. Fore leg grey-white, tibia with outer surface dark brown, tarsus with outer surface dark brown at base, scattered with brown scales distally; mid leg grey-white, outer surface dark brown; hind leg grey-white to pale yellow, tibia clothed with dark brown on outer surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,305,695,719]" box="[144,305,695,719]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
<emphasis box="[144,305,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Male genitalia</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,735,1015]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
(
<figureCitation box="[151,274,735,759]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="9.[144,211,1615,1637]" captionTargetBox="[156,1094,168,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[151,1095,168,1586]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Epichostis spp. (A) E. wufengensis, sp. nov.; (B) E. magnimacularis, sp. nov.; (C) E. tympanias (Meyrick); (D) E. proximitympanias, sp. nov.; (E) E. termitruncatula, sp. nov.; (F) E. termiprotrusa, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217048/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
). Uncus with basal two-fifths thick, distal three-fifths slender and pointed. Gnathos protruding forward at middle anteriorly, with a pair of long slender processes. Valva subtriangular, broad basally, narrowed distally to rounded apex; costa arched; dorsoproximal process somewhat ring-like, with bristles. Sacculus longer than costa slightly, broad and sclerotized, concave at about dorsal three-fifths, distal one-third narrowed and roundly pointed, with more heavily sclerotized edge. Juxta more or less heart-shaped, gently concave at middle on posterior margin, lateral lobe narrow. Aedeagus stout, obliquely truncate at apex, with a pointed apical process; cornutus long, made up of a bunch of spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,225,1071,1095]" box="[144,225,1071,1095]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
<emphasis box="[144,225,1071,1095]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,266,1111,1135]" box="[144,266,1111,1135]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,253,1183,1207]" box="[144,253,1183,1207]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
<emphasis box="[144,253,1183,1207]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,1223,1375]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meyrick)" authorityName="Sacculus" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[421,691,1223,1247]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Epichostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tympanias">
<emphasis box="[421,568,1223,1247]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">E. tympanias</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from it by the basal black patch not reaching two-thirds wing width dorsoapically, the valva narrower and the sacculus narrowed distally. In 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meyrick)" authorityName="Sacculus" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[654,923,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Epichostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tympanias">
<emphasis box="[654,800,1287,1311]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">E. tympanias</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
, the basal black patch exceeding two-thirds wing width dorsoapically, the valva broader and the sacculus about the same width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,265,1424,1448]" box="[144,265,1424,1448]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
<emphasis box="[144,265,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1103,1463,1520]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">
The specific name comes from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[677,756,1464,1488]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">proxim</emphasis>
- (= approximate) and the species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sacculus" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[259,373,1496,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Epichostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tympanias">
<emphasis box="[259,373,1496,1520]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2152">tympanias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating the similarities of the two species.
</paragraph>
